<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-11-02T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-11-02T00:00:00-05:00" n="183" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d183">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source"><persName corresp="#p_RFD1">Roosevelt</persName> Papers: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">President</gloss></hi><note n="1" xml:id="d183fn1">Sent by the United States Naval Attaché Moscow, via
                                Navy channels.</note></head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left"><hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                                <lb/>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">urgent</hi></seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-11-02">2 November 1943</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Most secret for the President only from <persName corresp="#p_HC1">Hull</persName></p>
                        <p>A message has been given me from the person highest in authority to be
                            delivered to you personally in extreme secrecy. The message promises to
                            get in and help to defeat the enemy.</p>
                        <p>Remainder follows in another code.<note n="2" xml:id="d183fn2"><persName corresp="#p_HC1">Hull</persName> wrote, in his <hi rend="italic">Memoirs</hi>, vol. <hi rend="smallcaps">ii</hi>, p. 1311: “The
                                information <persName corresp="#p_SIV1">Stalin</persName> had given
                                me on his decision regarding Japan I regarded as so secret that I
                                sent one-half of it to the President over the Navy code and the
                                other half over the Army code.”</note></p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>